## v2.1.1

### Removed
- Remove all `.woff` files (#25)

### Fixes
- Removed extra forward slash to fix file paths for some arabic files

## v2.1.0

### Added
- New subset for additional unicode ranges related to mathematics

### Fixes
- Fixed diacritical combining marks in Vietnamese

## v2.0.1

### Fixes
- Update Vietnamese subsets to solve problems with rendering certain glyphs

## v2.0.0

### Breaking Changes
- `SST Vietnamese` family removed ("Avenir Next" family now supports Vietnamese glyphs)

### Additions
- Vietnamese support in Avenir Next
- Thai support in Avenir Next
- Arabic support in Avenir Next
- Hebrew support in Avenir Next

## v1.4.2

### Added
- :chart_with_upwards_trend: Add tracking css to the CDN css file
- :spiral_notepad: Add usage notes to built files

## v1.4.1

### Fixed
- :wrench: Fix metrics/alignment for medium weight (#13)

## v1.4.0

### Added
- `$calcite-fonts-display` allows customizing font loading strategies via the `font-display` property

## v1.3.2

### Fixed
- :wrench: Fix baseline alignment of text in Microsoft Edge (#11)

## v1.3.1

### Fixed
- :wrench: Fix medium weight of basic subset (files were incorrectly subsetted)

## v1.3.0

### Added
- :new: **Avenir Next Medium** now available as `500` weight

### Fixed
- :wrench: Thai files fixed in Microsoft Edge (OpenType turned on)

## v1.2.0

### Added

- Added a separate css file which will be deployed to the CDN

## v1.1.2

### Fixed

- Fixed Arabic language rendering of Helvetica Neue Arabic and removed temporary Segoe UI fix

## v1.1.1

### Fixed

- Arabic languages on Windows now use Segoe UI instead of Helvetica Neue Arabic (#5)

## v1.1.0

### Added

- styles can now be imported with SASS + configurable font path

## v1.0.1

### Fixed

- commented out plain text in CSS file
- disable Thai (needed for proper rendering of all languages in Microsoft Edge)
- update Hebrew woff and woff2 files to include opentype support

## v1.0.0

### Added

- added all subset font files
- added `font-face` rules for every language
